          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-07-29T20:53:33Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Refueling Assistance Act of 2015</b></p> <p> Directs the Department of Transportation (DOT) to study motor vehicle refueling assistance to qualified individuals with disabilities.</p> <p>Requires the DOT to report to Congress the study results and any recommendations for imposing feasible and cost-effective requirements on gas stations to improve motor vehicle refueling assistance for such individuals.</p> <p>Authorizes the DOT to impose a civil penalty on persons who knowingly violate any regulations issued under this Act.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-07-27T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
